Defence lawyer Malesela Teffo JOHANNESBURG - The defence in the Senzo Meyiwa murder trial says their lives are at risk. Defence advocate, Malesela Teffo was arrested in court but it's unclear what charges he faces. This happened just after the case was adjourned for the day. READ: Police arrest defence lawyer in Meyiwa case Police came into the court and handcuffed Teffo before leading him away. When questioned by eNCA about why he was being arrested, Teffo said Police Minister Bheki Cele wanted him off the case. Tshepo Thobane, Teffo's lawyer, says the arrest is nothing more than intimidation tactics by the police.  Advocate Malesela #Teffo, who represents four of the five accused men in the Senzo Meyiwa murder trial, says Police Minister Bheki Cele doesn’t want him on the case. Police arrested the defence lawyer in court after the Meyiwa case was adjourned on Thursday. #DStv403 #eNCA pic.twitter.com/HQCGx6HGCP